The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for time series prediction in the context of dynamical systems. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of deep learning. The paper also discusses the use of constraints to improve the accuracy and efficiency of the neural network models, which is a common theme in optimization and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
